                            <comment id="15857269" author="thiru_mg" created="Wed, 8 Feb 2017 02:41:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d like to slip in a few fixes for outstanding C++ issues in the next release. I&apos;ll have them done by the weekend.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15860203" author="sacharya" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2017 21:05:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That works with me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15860564" author="sacharya" created="Fri, 10 Feb 2017 02:27:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For the last couple of hours I am trying to run &lt;tt&gt;./build.sh test&lt;/tt&gt; on the project and it has been failing for javascript and ruby to begin with.&lt;br/&gt;
That surely needs to be fixed prior to the release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16049649" author="radai" created="Wed, 14 Jun 2017 20:52:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;i&apos;d love to see a fix for this - &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-2035&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-2035&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16094233" author="sacharya" created="Thu, 20 Jul 2017 05:51:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=radai&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;radai&quot;&gt;radai rosenblatt&lt;/a&gt; sorry for the delayed response. &lt;br/&gt;
I do not want to backport the change to branch 1.7 because it is a backwards incompatible change and will break the contract of not pushing backwards incompatible change into a maintenance release.&lt;br/&gt;
If someone is able to backport it without making it incompatible in behaviour then I would be okay with it. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16202891" author="sacharya" created="Fri, 13 Oct 2017 00:55:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The cherry-picking of all the changes is now complete.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16367617" author="alex_rentz" created="Fri, 16 Feb 2018 17:27:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any updates on this release? I am running into the issue fixed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1642&quot; title=&quot;JVM Spec Violation 255 Parameter Limit Exceeded &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AVRO-1642&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AVRO-1642&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#160;and can&apos;t take the 1.8.x line.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
